        "name": "Wasp",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Paralytic Poison",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 343",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 343",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 343,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The poison of the giant wasp loses its potency soon after being harvested, but alchemists have learned of a way to preserve some of its properties by adding a number of harsh additives; this method makes it even deadlier.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Calistria",
                "aonid": 279,
                "game-obj": "Deities",
                "name": "Calistria",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Sacred Stingers",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 343",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 343",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 343,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Wasps are upheld as sacred among the priesthood of the elven deity Calistria, goddess of vengeance. Some priests of Calistria summon giant wasps or wasp swarms as servitors, while a few nurture giant wasps as pets, temple guardians, or companions. Followers of Calistria emulate the wasp's penchant for leaving stung victims alive to suffer over a long period\u2014a fitting model for revenge.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core pg. 343",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core pg. 343",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core",
            "page": 343,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "While the common wasp poses little threat to a hardy adventurer aside from an uncomfortable sting, a large and aggressive swarm of these territorial insects\u2014to say nothing of their oversized kin\u2014can lay low an entire party of heroes. The wasps represented here are of the common variety, also known as yellow jackets, but many other sorts of dangerous wasps exist, such as a Garundi variant that swarms in such great numbers that it can decimate entire villages.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
